{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-doc-page-template-tsx","path":"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/code-first","result":{"data":{"file":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/hotchocolate/v10/code-first/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Code-First"},"html":"<p>The code-first schema approach lets us build GraphQL schemas with .NET types and it gives us all the goodness of strong types and the confidence of using the C# compiler to validate our code. There is no need to switch to the GraphQL syntax in order to specify our schema, we can do everything in our favorite .NET language.</p>\n<p>Let us get started and have a look at the various approaches that we can use to build a schema. It is important to know that we can mix the various approaches with Hot Chocolate and use the best solution for a specific problem.</p>\n<h1 id=\"pure-code-first\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pure-code-first\" aria-label=\"pure code first permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><path d=\"M326.612 185.391c59.747 59.809 58.927 155.698.36 214.59-.11.12-.24.25-.36.37l-67.2 67.2c-59.27 59.27-155.699 59.262-214.96 0-59.27-59.26-59.27-155.7 0-214.96l37.106-37.106c9.84-9.84 26.786-3.3 27.294 10.606.648 17.722 3.826 35.527 9.69 52.721 1.986 5.822.567 12.262-3.783 16.612l-13.087 13.087c-28.026 28.026-28.905 73.66-1.155 101.96 28.024 28.579 74.086 28.749 102.325.51l67.2-67.19c28.191-28.191 28.073-73.757 0-101.83-3.701-3.694-7.429-6.564-10.341-8.569a16.037 16.037 0 0 1-6.947-12.606c-.396-10.567 3.348-21.456 11.698-29.806l21.054-21.055c5.521-5.521 14.182-6.199 20.584-1.731a152.482 152.482 0 0 1 20.522 17.197zM467.547 44.449c-59.261-59.262-155.69-59.27-214.96 0l-67.2 67.2c-.12.12-.25.25-.36.37-58.566 58.892-59.387 154.781.36 214.59a152.454 152.454 0 0 0 20.521 17.196c6.402 4.468 15.064 3.789 20.584-1.731l21.054-21.055c8.35-8.35 12.094-19.239 11.698-29.806a16.037 16.037 0 0 0-6.947-12.606c-2.912-2.005-6.64-4.875-10.341-8.569-28.073-28.073-28.191-73.639 0-101.83l67.2-67.19c28.239-28.239 74.3-28.069 102.325.51 27.75 28.3 26.872 73.934-1.155 101.96l-13.087 13.087c-4.35 4.35-5.769 10.79-3.783 16.612 5.864 17.194 9.042 34.999 9.69 52.721.509 13.906 17.454 20.446 27.294 10.606l37.106-37.106c59.271-59.259 59.271-155.699.001-214.959z\"/></svg></a>Pure Code-First</h1>\n<p>We call the first approach pure code-first since we do not bother about GraphQL schema types, we will just write clean C# code that automatically translates to GraphQL types.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In order to use this approach in the most effective way opt into C# nullable reference types.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In GraphQL everything starts with one of the three root types (Query, Mutation or Subscriptions). Root types represent the operations that we can do on our schema.</p>\n<p>So, if we wanted to create the query root type we would simply write a <code class=\"language-text\">Query</code> class.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"65158297260424920000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class Query\n{\n    public string Hello() => &quot;world&quot;;\n}`, `65158297260424920000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">string</span></span> <span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string\">\"world\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now let us create a new schema with that root type.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"48552981867770530000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`var schema = SchemaBuilder.New()\n  .AddQueryType<Query>()\n  .Create();`, `48552981867770530000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span></span> schema <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> SchemaBuilder<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">New</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">AddQueryType</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Create</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We now have registered an object type with our new schema that is based on our <code class=\"language-text\">Query</code> class. The schema would look like the following (if nullable reference type are turned on):</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"18581294504935154000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`type Query {\n  hello: String!\n}`, `18581294504935154000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sdl\"><pre class=\"language-sdl\"><code class=\"language-sdl\"><span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> String<span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We didn't even have to write resolvers due to the fact that the schema inferred those from the hello method. Our hello method is actually our resolver.</p>\n<p>This is just a simple class, with no real challenge to it. The schema builder is able to automatically infer interface usage, arguments, really everything just from our types.</p>\n<p>But what if we wanted to apply middleware to our types like paging, filtering or sorting?</p>\n<p>For this we have something called <em>descriptor attributes</em> so applying filtering to a field would look like the following example:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"75805527802186760000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class Query\n{\n    [UseFiltering]\n    public IQueryable<Foo> GetFoos()\n    {\n        ...\n    }\n}`, `75805527802186760000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token attribute\"><span class=\"token class-name\">UseFiltering</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\">IQueryable<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Foo<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span> <span class=\"token function\">GetFoos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token range operator\">..</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This attribute would add all the necessary filter input types and apply the filter middleware to that field.</p>\n<p>If you want to read more about how to use or build these attributes head over <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/schema/descriptor-attributes\">here</a>.</p>\n<h1 id=\"code-first\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#code-first\" aria-label=\"code first permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><path d=\"M326.612 185.391c59.747 59.809 58.927 155.698.36 214.59-.11.12-.24.25-.36.37l-67.2 67.2c-59.27 59.27-155.699 59.262-214.96 0-59.27-59.26-59.27-155.7 0-214.96l37.106-37.106c9.84-9.84 26.786-3.3 27.294 10.606.648 17.722 3.826 35.527 9.69 52.721 1.986 5.822.567 12.262-3.783 16.612l-13.087 13.087c-28.026 28.026-28.905 73.66-1.155 101.96 28.024 28.579 74.086 28.749 102.325.51l67.2-67.19c28.191-28.191 28.073-73.757 0-101.83-3.701-3.694-7.429-6.564-10.341-8.569a16.037 16.037 0 0 1-6.947-12.606c-.396-10.567 3.348-21.456 11.698-29.806l21.054-21.055c5.521-5.521 14.182-6.199 20.584-1.731a152.482 152.482 0 0 1 20.522 17.197zM467.547 44.449c-59.261-59.262-155.69-59.27-214.96 0l-67.2 67.2c-.12.12-.25.25-.36.37-58.566 58.892-59.387 154.781.36 214.59a152.454 152.454 0 0 0 20.521 17.196c6.402 4.468 15.064 3.789 20.584-1.731l21.054-21.055c8.35-8.35 12.094-19.239 11.698-29.806a16.037 16.037 0 0 0-6.947-12.606c-2.912-2.005-6.64-4.875-10.341-8.569-28.073-28.073-28.191-73.639 0-101.83l67.2-67.19c28.239-28.239 74.3-28.069 102.325.51 27.75 28.3 26.872 73.934-1.155 101.96l-13.087 13.087c-4.35 4.35-5.769 10.79-3.783 16.612 5.864 17.194 9.042 34.999 9.69 52.721.509 13.906 17.454 20.446 27.294 10.606l37.106-37.106c59.271-59.259 59.271-155.699.001-214.959z\"/></svg></a>Code-First</h1>\n<p>The second and original approach to code-first is by using our schema types.</p>\n<p>Schema types allow us to keep the GraphQL type configuration separate from our .NET types. This can be the right approach when we do not want any Hot Chocolate attributes on our business objects.</p>\n<p>As I said earlier we can mix these approaches which can enable us to achieve awesome complex schemas with minimal boilerplate code.</p>\n<p>Schema types can be created either by using the schema builder and add the configuration where we add the type ...</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"26977976065013375000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`var schema = SchemaBuilder.New()\n    .AddQueryType<Query>(d => d\n        .Field(f => f.Hello())\n        .Type<NonNullType<StringType>>())\n    .Create();`, `26977976065013375000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span></span> schema <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> SchemaBuilder<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">New</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">AddQueryType</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>d <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> d\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Field</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> f<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">Type</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>NonNullType<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>StringType<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Create</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>.. or, since these fluent chains could get very long and unreadable we could also opt to declare a new class <code class=\"language-text\">QueryType</code> that extends <code class=\"language-text\">ObjectType&lt;Query&gt;</code> and add it to our schema like the following.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"7172639168000750000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class QueryType : ObjectType<Query>\n{\n    protected override void Configure(IObjectTypeDescriptor<Query> descriptor)\n    {\n        descriptor.Field(f => f.Hello()).Type<NonNullType<StringType>>();\n    }\n}\n\nvar schema = SchemaBuilder.New()\n    .AddQueryType<QueryType>()\n    .Create();`, `7172639168000750000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">QueryType</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token type-list\"><span class=\"token class-name\">ObjectType<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">override</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">void</span></span> <span class=\"token function\">Configure</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">IObjectTypeDescriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span> descriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        descriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Field</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> f<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">Type</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>NonNullType<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>StringType<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span></span> schema <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> SchemaBuilder<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">New</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">AddQueryType</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>QueryType<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Create</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Furthermore, we can add fields that are not based on our .NET type <code class=\"language-text\">Query</code>.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"4722465856956681000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class QueryType : ObjectType<Query>\n{\n    protected override void Configure(IObjectTypeDescriptor<Query> descriptor)\n    {\n        descriptor.Field(f => f.Hello()).Type<NonNullType<StringType>>();\n        descriptor.Field(&quot;foo&quot;).Type<StringType>().Resolver(() => &quot;bar&quot;);\n    }\n}`, `4722465856956681000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">QueryType</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token type-list\"><span class=\"token class-name\">ObjectType<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">override</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">void</span></span> <span class=\"token function\">Configure</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">IObjectTypeDescriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Query<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span> descriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        descriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Field</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>f <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> f<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">Type</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>NonNullType<span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>StringType<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        descriptor<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Field</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"foo\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">Type</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>StringType<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Resolver</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token string\">\"bar\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Our new resulting schema would now look like the following:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"81719949075820410000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`type Query {\n  hello: String!\n  foo: String\n}`, `81719949075820410000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sdl\"><pre class=\"language-sdl\"><code class=\"language-sdl\"><span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> String<span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">foo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> String\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">foo</code> field would use the specified delegate to resolve the field value. The fluent API offers us the same feature set as the GraphQL schema syntax.</p>\n<p>Next, let us have a look at resolver arguments. GraphQL fields let us define arguments, so they are more like methods in C# than properties.</p>\n<p>If we add a parameter to our <code class=\"language-text\">Hello</code> method, the <code class=\"language-text\">SchemaBuilder</code> will translate that into a GraphQL field argument.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"75737322716723940000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class Query\n{\n    public string Hello(string name) => \\$&quot;Greetings {name}&quot;;\n}`, `75737322716723940000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">string</span></span> <span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">string</span></span> name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token interpolation-string\"><span class=\"token string\">$\"Greetings </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token expression language-csharp\">name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"64156385740583710000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`type Query {\n  hello(name: String!): String!\n}`, `64156385740583710000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sdl\"><pre class=\"language-sdl\"><code class=\"language-sdl\"><span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token attr-name\">name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> String<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> String<span class=\"token operator\">!</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In order to get access to the resolver context in our resolver, we can just add the <code class=\"language-text\">IResolverContext</code> as a method parameter and the query engine will automatically inject the context:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"96408636265708960000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied code example\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`public class Query\n{\n    public string Hello(IResolverContext context, string name) =>\n        \\$&quot;Greetings {name} {context.Service<FooService>().GetBar()}&quot;;\n}`, `96408636265708960000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"Copy\"\n              >\n                <svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Query</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token return-type class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">string</span></span> <span class=\"token function\">Hello</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">IResolverContext</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\"><span class=\"token keyword\">string</span></span> name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span>\n        <span class=\"token interpolation-string\"><span class=\"token string\">$\"Greetings </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token expression language-csharp\">name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token expression language-csharp\">context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token generic-method\"><span class=\"token function\">Service</span><span class=\"token generic class-name\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>FooService<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">GetBar</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This was just a quick introduction - There is a lot more that we can do with <em>pure code-first</em> and <em>code-first</em>. In order to learn more, head over to the following documentation articles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you want to read more about the <code class=\"language-text\">SchemaBuilder</code> head over <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/schema\">here</a>.</li>\n<li>If you are interested about resolvers in more detail <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/schema/resolvers\">this</a> might be the right place for you.</li>\n<li>If you want to know how to split up types then <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/schema/splitting-types\">this</a> might be what you are looking for.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You are all fired up and want to get started with a little tutorial walking you through an end-to-end example with <code class=\"language-text\">MongoDB</code> as your database? <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/tutorials\">Follow me</a>!</p>\n<p>OK, OK, you already have an idea on what to do and you are just looking for a way to setup this whole thing with ASP.NET Core? <a href=\"/docs/hotchocolate/v10/server\">This</a> is where you find more on that.</p>\n<p>If you want to set Hot Chocolate up with AWS Lambda or Azure Functions head over to our slack channel, we do not yet have documentation on that but there are example projects showing how to do that. We are constantly adding to our documentation and will include documentation on that soon.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/hotchocolate/v10/code-first/#pure-code-first\">Pure Code-First</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/hotchocolate/v10/code-first/#code-first\">Code-First</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://chillicream.com","repositoryUrl":"https://github.com/ChilliCream/hotchocolate","tools":{"slack":"https://join.slack.com/t/hotchocolategraphql/shared_invite/enQtNTA4NjA0ODYwOTQ0LTViMzA2MTM4OWYwYjIxYzViYmM0YmZhYjdiNzBjOTg2ZmU1YmMwNDZiYjUyZWZlMzNiMTk1OWUx